Coroutine


1. Coroutine Scope

   Lifecycle of coroutine
   
   viewModelScope -> connected to view model

  lifecycleScope .>Connected to Activity / Fragment

2. Dispatcher (Threading )
    Dispatcher.main > UI thread ( Ui update , navigation, showing dialog)
    Dispatcher.IO > network/ database (API calls , database & file operation)
   Dispatcher.Default > Cpu work (sorting, filtering, data processing)

Switching thread

——

viewmodelScope.launch{ // starts with main thread

Val users = withContext(Dispatcher.IO){ // switch to IO thread to perform api calls
  api.getUsers()
}

updateUI(users) // now update UI in main thread
}

